The paper discusses the development of novel security technologies for mobile networks and the gathering and analysis of information about cyber-attacks targeting mobile users and networks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Security (cs.CR) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the development of a data collection infrastructure and the use of virtualized mobile honeypots, which suggests that it may also belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) and Systems and Control (cs.SI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the modus operandi of cyber-criminals, which suggests that it may also belong to the Cybersecurity (cs.CY) sub-category.
